　　The outbreak of swine flu that was first detected in Mexico was declared a global epidemic on June 11, 2009. It is the first worldwide epidemic  <mark>1</mark>  by the World Health Organization in 41 years.
　　The heightened alert  <mark>2</mark>  an emergency meeting with flu experts in Geneva that assembled after a sharp rise in cases in Australia, and rising    <mark>3</mark>   in Britain, Japan, Chile and elsewhere.
